Build step 2 of the local agent system: add a Telegram transport.

Requirements:
- Keep the current TypeScript local-agent core and reuse the existing Main Agent and Meta Agent flow.
- Integrate Telegram Bot API as the transport layer.
- Support receiving messages from Telegram and sending replies back to Telegram.
- Add a transport mode switch so the app can run in:
  - CLI mode
  - Telegram mode
- In Telegram mode, keep printing the conversation to stdout for observability (step 2b).
- Restrict Telegram access to exactly one allowed user/chat in this step.
- Reject or ignore messages from any other Telegram sender/chat.
- Keep session handling per Telegram conversation/user.
- After every accepted Telegram message:
  - run Main Agent
  - persist a trace
  - run Meta Agent
  - save a proposed config patch
- Keep the architecture modular so Signal or web transports can be added later.
- Add clear config for:
  - Telegram Bot token
  - allowed Telegram chat/user id
  - mode selection
  - polling interval and offset persistence
- Prefer long polling for local development reliability (no public HTTPS required).
- Keep strong typing, clean architecture, and comments.
